========================================================
FCFS - First Come First Served
========================================================
Non-preemptive. Among available processes, run the earliest arriving process first. Ties use input order.

Execution timeline:
  [ 0,  5)  P1
  [ 5,  9)  P2
  [ 9, 11)  P3
  [11, 14)  P4

Compact Gantt view:
  |0 P1 |5 P2 |9 P3 |11 P4 |14

Per-process results:
Process        Arr   Burst    Prio  Deadline  FirstStart    Finish   Waiting  Turnaround  Response   Missed
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
P1               0       5       2        20           0         5         0           5         0       no
P2               3       4       1        20           5         9         2           6         2       no
P3               6       2       3        20           9        11         3           5         3       no
P4               6       3       2        20          11        14         5           8         5       no

Summary metrics:
  Makespan              : 14
  Total busy time       : 14
  CPU utilization       : 100.00%
  Throughput            : 0.29 processes/unit-time
  Average waiting time  : 2.50
  Average turnaround    : 6.00
  Average response time : 2.50
  Deadline misses       : 0 / 4


========================================================
SJF - Shortest Job First
========================================================
Non-preemptive. Whenever the CPU becomes free, run the available process with the smallest burst time.

Execution timeline:
  [ 0,  5)  P1
  [ 5,  9)  P2
  [ 9, 11)  P3
  [11, 14)  P4

