  Deadline misses       : 0 / 4


========================================================
Round Robin
========================================================
Preemptive. Each ready process gets at most quantum=3 time units per turn. Arrivals at a time-slice boundary are queued before the preempted process.

Execution timeline:
  [ 0,  3)  P1
  [ 3,  6)  P2
  [ 6,  8)  P1
  [ 8, 10)  P3
  [10, 13)  P4
  [13, 14)  P2

Compact Gantt view:
  |0 P1 |3 P2 |6 P1 |8 P3 |10 P4 |13 P2 |14

Per-process results:
Process        Arr   Burst    Prio  Deadline  FirstStart    Finish   Waiting  Turnaround  Response   Missed
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
P1               0       5       2        20           0         8         3           8         0       no
P2               3       4       1        20           3        14         7          11         0       no
P3               6       2       3        20           8        10         2           4         2       no
P4               6       3       2        20          10        13         4           7         4       no

Summary metrics:
  Makespan              : 14
  Total busy time       : 14
  CPU utilization       : 100.00%
  Throughput            : 0.29 processes/unit-time
  Average waiting time  : 4.00
  Average turnaround    : 7.50
  Average response time : 1.50
  Deadline misses       : 0 / 4


==================== POLICY COMPARISON ====================
Policy                              Avg Wait  Avg Turnaround      Avg Resp    Misses      Util %
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
FCFS - First Come First Served          2.50            6.00          2.50         0      100.00
SJF - Shortest Job First                2.50            6.00          2.50         0      100.00
Priority Scheduling                     2.75            6.25          2.75         0      100.00
Round Robin                             4.00            7.50          1.50         0      100.00

Interpretation hints:
  - Lower waiting/turnaround time is usually better for batch-style workloads.
  - Lower response time is important for interactive workloads.
  - Round Robin often improves response time, but can increase turnaround time.
  - Deadline misses show whether a policy is suitable for time-bound workloads.
